title: The Rolling Stones - Exile on Main St. (Expanded) (1972, 320kps)
description: One of the most powerful sets in modern popular music, and the Stones' only double record.  Recorded in the south of France because of the group's status as tax exiles, this disc marks the highlight of Mick Taylor's tenure and the last truly great album of the group. Sex, death, and dissolution are familiar tropes for the boys and this album provides a majestic ending to an incendiary career - if only they had quit at this point
